description:
Dated and all around average to sub-par if you really want the T spilled. 

// The selection wasn't super interesting or informative. 

// They didn't have simple syrup out for sweetening iced coffees. 

// The place (tables and coffee condiment station) were pretty crumb-y and needed a good scrub. 

// They didn't have lights on which might be fine on a sunny day but it was cloudy and rainy and inside was next level dreary. It was like an episode of The Killing... which I realize is a very dated reference at this point the guy detective is still hot AF and it was definitely not the sister and the politician's helper guy who dun it so definitely nooo spoilers here if you're 5 years behind on TV. 

// It wasn't a comfortable place at all. Definitely made we want to finish my coffee ASAP and GTFO of there... and maybe that's what they're going for. I don't know but I like a cozy nook and warm environment with my bevvie. This place was as icey as my iced coffee.

// The one employee working was super on brand with the experience giving off some top notch dismal and abysmal vibes and immediately after he finished our order he went back to full-on eating a meal and reading on a case they store food in and I'm about 85% sure the health department is not cool with employees of a biz eating behind the counter when food and beverage service is involved. 

I don't see myself making a return visit to Moka. The reality of my visit was very different than the imagery on their online profile had led me to believe I would experience.
